  <bioghist id="8695047af81e9fbfad52fca74ccdd19f">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>William Clyde Pendleton (1923-2011) worked at the Ford Foundation for over ten years. He joined the Foundation as a Program Associate in the Economic Development and Administration Program. Following a change in the Foundation's program structure, he became a Program Officer in the Division of National Affairs, Urban and Metropolitan Development Program in 1966. He served in that position until 1974 when he moved to the Office of Resources and the Environment where he worked as a Program Officer. After another change in the Foundation's program structure, Pendleton spent his last years at the Foundation as a Program Officer in the Division of National Affairs.</p><p>Prior to joining the Ford Foundation, Pendleton taught at the University of Florida and the University of Pittsburgh. He served in the U.S. Navy during World War II.</p><p>Pendleton earned a B.A. in history from Brown University and a Ph.D. in economics from the University of Chicago.</p>  </bioghist>
